Raymond STITH, alias Raymond Stitts, v. The UNITED STATES of America. No. 4196. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Nov. 8, 1950. Robert Sunshine, Denver, Colo., for appellant. Max M. Bulkeley, U. S. Atty., Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and BRATTON and HUXMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed November 8, 1950, on motion of appellee, for failure to prosecute.
